# Skill Distiller (Cursor)

## Overview

Memory captures facts. Skills capture workflows. In Cursor, skills are
rules with `alwaysApply: false` so the agent pulls them in by description
match.

## When to Use

- A multi-step instruction has appeared in three separate sessions
- User asks "can you remember how I like to do X?"

## Steps

1. Survey peer rules in `.cursor/rules/skills/`.
2. Pick a verb-led slug.
3. Write `.cursor/rules/skills/<slug>.mdc` with:
   - `description:` starting with "Use when..." (this IS the trigger)
   - `alwaysApply: false`
   - Body with Overview / When to Use / Steps / Pitfalls / Checklist
4. Show the draft to the user before committing.

## Pitfalls

1. Distilling on the second occurrence.
2. `alwaysApply: true` on skills. Reserve `alwaysApply: true` for the
   persona, the protocol, and the memory index. Skills load on demand.
3. Descriptions that don't start with "Use when...". Cursor matches on
   the first sentence of the description.

## Checklist

- [ ] Trigger appeared three or more times
- [ ] `description` starts with "Use when"
- [ ] `alwaysApply: false`
- [ ] Body has all five sections
